    <h3 class="header" term="create_video">5. Create Project Video</h3>
    <div class="content" term="create_video">
      <h4 class="header" term="without_video">Without Video?</h4>
      <div class="content" term="without_video">
        <p>The project video plays vital role of success. Projects with video received much higher successful rate than those without, 59% (with video) vs. 32% (without video) . That’s why we still strongly encourage you to make a project video rather than not, even the video is not required for publishing your project on BULLCENTURY. After all, your will find it time worth.</p>
        <p>However, if you prefer not to do so. In order to make your project presentation more attractive, the empty video window (on project page) will be automatically replaced by your project image on the same spot.</p>
      </div>
      <h4 class="header" term="video_format">Video Format</h4>
      <div class="content" term="video_format">
        <ul>
          <li>mp4. mov. flv. mpg. webm. avi. ogv. are top preferred and recommend for the best quality</li>
          <li>Besides above listed, BULLCENTURY almost accepts and supports all other video formats. Please feel free to try which one works best for you. The video quality depends on many factors, such as operation system, uploading device, production software etc.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <h4 class="header" term="video_size">Video Size</h4>
      <div class="content" term="video_size">
        <p>< 5 GB per video</p>
      </div>
      <h4 class="header" term="device_i_need">What device do I need to make a video?</h4>
      <div class="content" term="device_i_need">
        <p>You could directly produce or upload videos from all smart devices such as tablets, smartphone, video camera or laptop/desktop, regardless your equipment is professional or un-professional, expensive or
        cheap, simple or complicated.</p>
      </div>
      <h4 class="header" term="shooting_by_smartphone">Shooting Video by Smartphone or Tablets</h4>
      <div class="content" term="shooting_by_smartphone">
        <p>Bullcentury supports and receives video-uploading directly from your smart phones, tablets and all other smart camera devices. But please note that keep your smart device horizontal while shooting video, so the final video could fit on project screen in nice and wide shape.</p>
      </div>
      <h4 class="header" term="video_experience">Do I need to have video experience or a professional video camera man?</h4>
      <div class="content" term="video_experience">
        <p>No, video production experience is not required to produce a project video. Don’t be afraid to express yourself in front of the camera. An amateur video can be as attractive as those been professionally made if you could keep the following key factors in mind:</p>
        <ol>
          <li>Be yourself, be open, and be honest</li>
          <li>Describe your project as detailed as possible</li>
          <li>Maximize the video, sound and light quality within your equipment capacity</li>
        </ol>
      </div>
      <h4 class="header" term="video_content">Video Content Guideline</h4>
      <div class="content" term="video_content">
        <p>Even you may use all kinds creativities to impress audience in the video. For the better success, we still recommend you to cover the following contents:</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Self Introduction & Project Introduction</li>
          <li>Story Behind your project (e.g. motives, personal feelings, idea comes from... etc.)</li>
          <li>Ask for support, set a clear list and content about the helps you need</li>
          <li>Explain the reason why you need their supports and money</li>
          <li>Explain what will you do or achieve with their money</li>
          <li>Offer your reward in details, make them as attractive as possible. (Additional images can be used)</li>
          <li>Inform your settings including funding goal, time limit, what if the funding goal did not reached... etc.</li>
          <li>Express your appreciation at the end</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <h4 class="header" term="better_video">Better Video better success?</h4>
      <div class="content" term="better_video">
        <p>Yes, in all perspectives, a better looking video will benefit your project by increasing the attractiveness and popularity. Therefore, if you have the ability to add some professional touch up, worth to do so.</p>
        <p>For more information:</p>
        <p><a href="#">How to shoot better project video</a> (BC University Level II: BETTER project video)</p>
        <p><a href="#">BC Media Studio</a> (BC Authorized Professional Help)</p>
      </div>
      <h4 class="header" term="do_not_do_this">Do <u>not</u> do these things in your video</h4>
      <div class="content" term="do_not_do_this">
        <p>Do not put any unauthorized (copyrighted) music, animation characters, or image in your video. The big fine and lawsuit by the copyright owner may cost you trouble later on.</p>
