    <h3 class="header" term="create_reward">6. Create Reward</h3>
    <div class="content" term="create_reward">
      <p>Creating Reward is another crucial part which has heavy influence on the final success. Projects that offer unrealistic, uninspired, overpriced or underpriced rewards usually fail to attract support. The importances of value mix are creative, meaningful and fairly valued.</p>
      <h4 class="header" term="the-common-reward-offers">What are the common reward offers?</h4>
      <div class="content" term="the-common-reward-offers">
        <strong>1. Tangible Product</strong>
        <p>New product that made from your project.</p>
        <p>Examples: new innovative product, first CD album, DVD, Show Ticket</p>
        <strong>2. Creative Involvement</strong>
        <p>Collaborate supporters into your project creations.</p>
        <p>Examples: play a role in your movie; show supporters faces in my photo album; paint supporter’s portraits on all T-shirt; be the models of my fashion show</p>
        <strong>3. Creative Experiences</strong>
        <p>Invite supporter to experience your project creations.</p>
        <p>Examples: a free ride of my new air-balloon night-tour; invite all to my concert; invite supporter’s children to try new swing chair in the community play ground.</p>
        <strong>4. Meaningful Mementos</strong>
        <p>Offering something with meaningful memory and joyful moment.</p>
        <p>Examples: post card with whole team picture after reached mountain peak - Everest; meaningful token tells our final victory; a picture of rescued dolphin.</p>
      </div>
      <h4 class="header" term="price-a-reward">How to Price a Reward</h4>
      <div class="content" term="price-a-reward">
        <ul>
          <li>Offering something has value more than sticker price - first one in the world to try, limited edition etc.</li>
          <li>Offering realistic price or close to manufacture cost - Be creative, but be reasonable. ‘Rip-off’ will cost permanent damage to the project credibility.</li>
        </ul>

